You are building Phase 13 of the LoveGenie dating app. Read CLAUDE.md for full project context. Phases 0-12 are complete (full backend is done).

Build the mobile app's auth flow: API client, auth context, navigation, and auth screens.

## 1. mobile/src/types/index.ts

Define TypeScript interfaces matching the backend schemas:
- `User`: id, email, first_name, last_name, gender, age, is_email_verified, is_selfie_verified, is_admin
- `PublicProfile`: id, first_name, age, gender, program, year_of_study, bio, photo_urls, interests, is_selfie_verified
- `PrivateProfile extends PublicProfile`: age_range_min, age_range_max
- `DateRequest`: id, user_id, group_size, activity, status, availability_slots, created_at
- `AvailabilitySlot`: date, time_window
- `DateGroup`: id, activity, scheduled_date, scheduled_time, venue_name, venue_address, status, members (PublicProfile[])
- `Match`: id, partner (PublicProfile), chat_room_id, group_id, created_at
- `ChatRoom`: id, room_type, last_message, group_id, participants
- `ChatMessage`: id, sender_id, sender_name, content, created_at
- `ActivityType`: union of all activity strings
- `TimeWindow`: "morning" | "afternoon" | "evening" | "night"

## 2. mobile/src/api/client.ts

- Create an axios instance with `baseURL` set to `http://localhost:8000` (configurable)
- Add request interceptor: if token exists in AsyncStorage, add `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
- Add response interceptor: on 401, clear token and navigate to login
- Export the configured instance

## 3. mobile/src/api/auth.ts

- `register(data)` — POST /api/auth/register
- `verifyEmail(email, otp)` — POST /api/auth/verify-email
- `login(email, password)` — POST /api/auth/login, store token in AsyncStorage
- `getMe()` — GET /api/auth/me
- `logout()` — clear token from AsyncStorage

## 4. mobile/src/context/AuthContext.tsx

React Context providing:
- `user: User | null`
- `token: string | null`
- `isLoading: boolean` (checking stored token on app start)
- `login(email, password): Promise<void>`
- `register(data): Promise<{otp: string}>`
- `verifyEmail(email, otp): Promise<void>`
- `logout(): void`

On mount: check AsyncStorage for existing token, if found call getMe() to validate, set user.

## 5. mobile/src/navigation/AppNavigator.tsx

- If not authenticated: show Auth stack (LoginScreen → RegisterScreen → VerifyEmailScreen)
- If authenticated but no profile: show ProfileSetupScreen (will be built in phase 14, just show placeholder text for now)
- If authenticated with profile: show Main tab navigator with tabs: Home, My Dates, Chat, Profile (placeholders for now, just Text components)

Use `@react-navigation/native-stack` for stack, `@react-navigation/bottom-tabs` for tabs.

## 6. Mobile Screens

### mobile/src/screens/LoginScreen.tsx
- Email input, password input, login button
- "Don't have an account? Register" link → navigate to Register
- On submit: call auth context login, handle errors (show alert)
- Clean, simple design using React Native StyleSheet

### mobile/src/screens/RegisterScreen.tsx
- Fields: first_name, last_name, email (.edu hint), password, phone, gender (picker: Male/Female), age
- Email validation hint: "Use your university email (.utoronto.ca, .edu)"
- On submit: call register, navigate to VerifyEmailScreen with email + OTP (for dev display)

### mobile/src/screens/VerifyEmailScreen.tsx
- Email display (readonly), OTP input (6 digits)
- In dev mode: show the OTP from registration response for easy testing
- On submit: call verifyEmail, on success navigate to Login with success message

## 7. mobile/App.tsx

Wrap everything in AuthProvider and NavigationContainer:
```tsx
<AuthProvider>
  <NavigationContainer>
    <AppNavigator />
  </NavigationContainer>
</AuthProvider>
```

## 8. Tests

### mobile/__tests__/api/auth.test.ts
- Mock axios. Test that register calls POST /api/auth/register with correct payload
- Test that login stores token in AsyncStorage
- Test that logout clears AsyncStorage

### mobile/__tests__/screens/LoginScreen.test.tsx
- Renders email and password inputs
- Renders login button
- Renders register link

## 9. Jest Configuration

Update `mobile/jest.config.js` if needed:
- Mock `@react-native-async-storage/async-storage`
- Mock `@react-navigation` modules
- Set `transformIgnorePatterns` to handle node_modules that need transformation

IMPORTANT:
- All API calls go through the axios client with token interceptor
- AsyncStorage is the token store — no other persistence mechanism
- Navigation structure: AuthStack (not logged in) vs MainTabs (logged in)
- TypeScript must compile: `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass
- Keep styles simple — no external UI library, just StyleSheet
